# Conditional Statements

## if Statement

**Execute code if condition is true**

```javascript
if (condition) {
    // code runs if true
}

const age = 18;
if (age >= 18) {
    console.log('You are an adult');
}
```

## if-else Statement

**Choose between two paths**

```javascript
if (condition) {
    // runs if true
} else {
    // runs if false
}

const score = 45;
if (score >= 50) {
    console.log('Pass');
} else {
    console.log('Fail');
}
```

## else-if Ladder

**Multiple conditions**

```javascript
if (condition1) {
    // block 1
} else if (condition2) {
    // block 2
} else if (condition3) {
    // block 3
} else {
    // default
}

const marks = 75;
if (marks >= 90) {
    console.log('Grade A');
} else if (marks >= 80) {
    console.log('Grade B');
} else if (marks >= 70) {
    console.log('Grade C');
} else {
    console.log('Fail');
}
```

## switch Statement

**Multi-way selection**

```javascript
switch (expression) {
    case value1:
        // code
        break;
    case value2:
        // code
        break;
    default:
        // code
}

const day = 3;
switch (day) {
    case 1:
        console.log('Monday');
        break;
    case 2:
        console.log('Tuesday');
        break;
    case 3:
        console.log('Wednesday');
        break;
    default:
        console.log('Invalid');
}
```

## Ternary Operator

**Shorthand if-else**

```javascript
const age = 20;
const status = age >= 18 ? 'Adult' : 'Minor';
console.log(status);  // Adult
```

