# Objects

## Object Creation

**Using literal notation**

```javascript
const person = {
    name: 'John',
    age: 30,
    city: 'New York'
};

console.log(person.name);       // John
console.log(person['age']);     // 30
```

## Object Properties

**Add/modify properties**

```javascript
const car = { brand: 'Toyota' };
car.model = 'Camry';            // Add property
car.year = 2023;
car.brand = 'Honda';            // Modify property

console.log(car);  // { brand: 'Honda', model: 'Camry', year: 2023 }
```

## Object Methods

**Functions as properties**

```javascript
const student = {
    name: 'Alice',
    age: 20,
    greet: function() {
        return 'Hi, I am ' + this.name;
    }
};

console.log(student.greet());  // Hi, I am Alice
```

## Looping Objects

```javascript
const user = {
    name: 'Bob',
    email: 'bob@example.com',
    age: 25
};

for (let key in user) {
    console.log(key + ': ' + user[key]);
}
```

