# Class Inheritance

Inheritance allows a class to inherit properties and methods from another class using the `extends` keyword.

---

## 1. The 'extends' Keyword

```javascript
class Animal {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }
  eat() { console.log(`${this.name} is eating`); }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
  bark() { console.log('Woof!'); }
}
```

## 2. Working with super()

The `super` keyword is used to call functions on an object's parent.

- **constructor**: Used to call the parent constructor (mandatory if child has its own constructor).
- **methods**: Can call parent methods using `super.methodName()`.

```javascript
class Admin extends User {
  constructor(name, email, level) {
    super(name, email); // Calls parent constructor
    this.level = level;
  }
}
```

