# Modular JavaScript

Before modules, JS files shared everything globally. ES Modules allow us to keep variables private unless explicitly exported.

---

## 1. Named Exports

```javascript
// math.js
export const PI = 3.14;
export function add(a, b) { return a + b; }

// main.js
import { PI, add } from './math.js';
```

## 2. Default Exports

Each file can have ONE default export.

```javascript
// Config.js
export default { apiKey: '123', debug: true };

// main.js
import settings from './Config.js';
```

